caption: Food was delicious. Good service.
The customer service is top notch. The food is just ok at best but they are very speedy and curteous.
Place was very elegant. Servers were very pleasant. Room reserved for party was a little tight. Food was very good. Overall good presentation.
Dinner was excellent!

Our experience was TERRIBLE. Me and my boyfriend went there this past Saturday night and the entire experience was very disappointing. I made reservations for 9 pm. We get there 10 mins prior to our reservation and was told we were checked in but still had to wait to be seated. It didn't become an issues until we were standing there waiting for at least 30 mins after our reservation time. As we were we standing there I noticed several other parties of two, three, and four also coming in for reservations at 9 as well. .... what is the point of a reservation if I can't be seated at the exact time?? When we were finally seated at a table, it took a while for anyone to come to the table. When he finally came, he took drink orders and brought the wrong drinks. We ordered our food so we wouldn't have to wait and we ended up waiting an additional 30 mins for our food. I ordered a steak with the lobster mac n cheese and the grilled asparagus. My asparagus was cold. The lobster mac n cheese needed more seasoning. I felt as if the food was cooked and rushed because the kitchen closed at 10. I was really looking forward to dining here, but the experience wasn't even worth the time and money. I will not be returning to this location.

Had a good time here. Everyone was extra friendly and talkative. The maî·tre d' was male and had us laughing before we sat down. Server was extremely helpful. She walked us through the entire menu. Knew it by heart, including ingredients, cuts, where the meat came from. It's like you couldn't stump her in detail. Menu was pretty straight forward. One page, as most restaurants are doing in these Covid-19 times, trying to simplify. The food was delicious and cave out quick. Everything on the menu is à la carte which add up quickly in price, but I feel it was worth it. Restaurants ambiance was perfect. Booth seating was plush and comfortable. Again, great experience and if I'm ever out there again I most definitely will go back.
Just an incredible experience! Our wait staff Jamie was knowledgeable and attentive. Definitely will be returning!!!

The food and atmosphere is perfect for a date night! Food was very good! Even though it’s kind of expensive, it was worth every penny. My waitress (Tor-A) was very friendly and helpful. I will be returning again!
Great customer service and  their food is fantastic

Absolutely fantastic food and service! Charlie (manager) stopped by to check on us and make sure everything was holding to high standard, which gave an already special day out a wonderful compliment of food service. We were treated to a baked Alaska on our special day that was absolutely superb. Will be returning without question.
Seafood is fresh and delicious! Prices are high but worth it for special occasions.

I frequent this restaurant, but this time, I decided to try a new dish, the lobster pot pie. To my dismay, it was NOT tasty. My server sensed my displeasure, immediately, and asked if I wanted to replace it with something else from the menu. I ordered the chickenchicken-fried lobster, which was AMAZING! Kudos to the chef and waitstaff for always taking care of their customers!
From start to finish an A plus!  Our Server Stephanie was outstanding!  She truly made the experience a wonderful time!  Dinner service was spectacular.  A lovely time downtown.

First time ever in Baltimore, for me! My husband treated me to this restaraunt and i have to say..the staff was unbelievable! The food was excellent!  We would like to let the managers and the owner know that Cassie, Makayla, and Jamie are a huge asset to your team!  They went above and beyond to make sure everything was perfect! I would advise anyone wanting to try this place, do not eat a big lunch, before you eat here! It is a 10+ for food and service!

I went here to celebrate my birthday about two weeks ago.Was a little disappointed at the slowness of service,wasn't sure why because it was hardly anyone in the restaurant,but I must say they redeemed themselves.Food was excellent,their calamari was the best I ever tasted it was delicious.We left the restaurant being full and satisfied.

As advertised, which is to say it's excellent in every way. Highly recommend and worth the price tag. If you're looking for a spot for a special occasion, you won't go wrong picking this one. Impressed! We really enjoyed ourselves last night!! Charlie and his team were responsive, upbeat and made us feel valued as customers. The sides were average but the main dishes shined. My favorite was the bone in ribeye! Lobster Mac is also a must try. We’ll be back.

It was the perfect place to celebrate our anniversary. The food was really good and the restaurant is beautiful. Our server was excellent, she brought us a Baked Alaska dessert for our anniversary and it was superb. They are in the pricey side, but great for celebrating our date night.
We went the first night they opened after the covid lock down. Very friendly staff. The food was hot and fresh and the drinks were amazing..will go again next time we are in town

Unfortunately we could not dine in due to COVID-19 so we got take out. Over all the staff was extremely pleasant and friendly. I tried the seafood boil for the first time there...it was a healthy portion of seafood and fresh however there was no flavor at all and it was my very first time ever having carrots in a seafood boil. I would definitely go back but I’ll try another dish.

I’m sure these avenues of communication are often used for the perception of negative, but I’d  like to share an incredibly positive experience I’ve had at your Baltimore location over the past two nights.  There is a server from Trinidad and Tobago that has been cross-training as a bartender recently, not sure her name.  Andrew the manager mentioned this to me when he introduced himself which was a considerate gesture.  The food, the service, and the personal connection at this location has been second to none.  I travel for a living and have many trepidations about dining out. The Baltimore location comes with nice people and a very safe environment.  It seems like the staff there care about each other, the customers, and your business...which is a rare combo.  I work for the NFL and eat at the Indy location every year during our Scouting Combine.  I will now eat at the Baltimore location for the next two nights, and bring every colleague I can thanks to Andrew and the wonderful woman behind the bar.  Kudos to you for whatever you did to hire these wonderful people.

The Oceanaire was phenomenal. The service staff were genuine, friendly, courteous and professional. It was definitely a FINE DINING experience for my Wife birthday. This is a high quality dining experience on the backdrop of the Baltimore harbor. We will definitely be back. Thank you Oceanaire Baltimore!!

It was so nice! Between the amazing food, and the simply amazing server, Cassie, I can't wait to come back. They went out of their way to make our visit memorable,  and my daddy's birthday special. Definitely come by if you're by Harbor East!

I was very impressed with the staff and the general manager Andrew (I believe that is his name). I ordered takeout a few times. Just enough food for me, my bill was small, but they still treated me as if I was spending a thousand dollars. The blackened salmon salad is fantastic!!!

It's a pricey restaurant and depending on what you order you might not get your money's worth on your plate, so be very careful to make sure you tell the server what your appetite is for that day...Also be sure to ask how your food is being prepared because mines was grilled and I wasn't happy with my Lobster, shrimp, scallops and asparagus being charcoal grilled with a burned taste and burned edges on it...Not a 5 star seafood taste...Also, be sure to have at least 100 dollars or more when ordering food and drinks exspecially liquor. The food was good as well as the server and we tipped well even though I wasn't impressed with my food... Well let's start with the service. It was slow, and I know its a pandemic but I mean unbelievably slow. I ordered the sea scallops I can't quite remember the price but it was priced between $37-42 on my plate were 5 scallops a lemon wedge and parsley garnish and the plate was lukewarm. But it did taste fairly well I will say that much. I also had the asparagus which was $13 for 7 spears. My wife ordered shrimp scampi at a similar price the plate was Mohave dessert dry the pasta looked like Ramen and the shrimp were over cooked scampi is supposed to saturated in garlic butter right? DRRRRRRYYYYYY!!. My uncle ordered the chefs crab cakes(we live in Baltimore) the dish was priced above $40 for 2 SLIGHTLY larger than golfball sized almost non seasoned crab cakes. I wish I knew Chef Gordon Ramsey personally, I would unleash him on this place in a glorious display of wrath and vengeance. The food could have been seasoned better with larger portions atleast. I didn't list everyone out of our party of 12 but needless to say we were all disappointed with our experience and had to go elsewhere to get our fill. The best part of the night was the $15 cocktail it was small but it was awesome so if I went back it would be for the drinks.
quality meals, so good. i give this place double thumbs up. i will probably become a regular. prices that won't break you. like a restaurant in washington i liked.

I had to wait about 20 minutes before I got a water refill.   It is unsatisfactory that a restaurant whose price point is pretty high to have such poor service. There's nothing wrong with the food.  It's well cooked and well executed.  The service is friendly and knowledgeable.  But man, for the prices they charge people should expect to be AMAZED.  And my experience tonight was far from that.  My wife ordered the "diver" scallops, and at $40 for 5 quarter-sized scallops by themselves on a plate they should have been just the best darn scallops we ever had. They were so ordinary it was painful. 6 sticks of grilled asparagus for $12?  They should be way better than what I'd expect from the Olive Garden, and they weren't. Our server just didn't have the time to tend to our table properly (multiple empty drinks in front of us, the wrong items being served to the wrong people, etc.)  I honestly don't think it was his fault, but from the customers point of view does it matter?  All in all, it was a very ordinary dinner with very ordinary service, in a fancy-decor restaurant with exorbitant prices.  If you have a corporate card burning a hole in your pocket and want to impress your clients by showing them how irresponsibly you can spend the company's money, then this is a great spot.  If you want to spend real money on a memorable dining experience, there are FAR better options in Baltimore.

The service, food, and atmosphere is great. Had chicken fried lobster tails. Very good. Would never have thought of eating lobster that way. Pricey but worth it.

To start with, Adam our server was AMAZING. He was exuberant and as excited about our food as we were. He made excellent suggestions for us when the restaurant didn't have the exact wine or spirit we were looking for. He was just great and I hope to work with him next time we visit.  Next our food was delightful. The chef special, Chilean seabass with seared scallops and crabmeat on top was to die for. I love Chilean seabass and this one was well prepared and the flavor of the fish was complemented by the other seafood and not over powered as can happen with some flavors.  It was just a great seafood meal. It really should be on the regular menu. If it was, I would probably get it every time.  We shared a side of the Gouda mac and cheese. A perfect accompaniment for our meal  I look forward to visiting again.
Great dinner, excellent staff, the place to go for a special night out.

Attended an organized group event here. The food was absolutely delicious, but the service was extremely slow. I probably attribute this to serving such a large group (~50 people), and so I wouldn’t recommend hosting a large event here. For reference, cocktail hour was an hour and a half because we were seated 30 min late, it took another 50 min to bring out preselected soup/salad, and then another 45 min to bring out entrees. To be fair, some groups might prefer this speed! I will probably return to try the normal seating experience, because again, food was fantastic.

My complements to the chef for whipping up an amazing vegetarian dish. I was thought they only had pasta primavera for a vegetarian option, but the chef blew me away with stuffed green peppers rice dish. Bottom line, they know how to take care of everyone in the party.

The proteins are cooked and seasoned to perfection. The steak was flawless.  However, the supporting starch sides and vegetables are really lackluster and leave more than a little to be desired. The restaurant is quite large, so don’t expect the same level of attention to cooking or service as you might find in a smaller restaurant.  Overall, it was an overpriced meal for the quality of food we received. Remember that you’re also paying for the location when you dine here...

We chose a mix of hot and cold appetizer which included cracked snow crab legs, tuna sashimi, crab cakes and shrimp cocktails. Which was all served by hand. I chose a filet topped with crab cakes. Sides are family style and we chose steamed spinach, risotto, mashed potatoes. For dessert we had baked Alaska and cookies. Can't say enough.

The temperature outside was 100F but we were sitting  comfortably apart from other tables. It is important to me because I have been in fancy places where they put you like sardines and there is no privacy. As for food I think Oysters Rockefeller were outstanding. Again, the menu is standard seafood/steak house, but what they do they do very well. Last Thursday I had a dinner consisting of a jumbo shrimp cocktal, a wagyu filet and giant shrimp from Madagascar (!). Simple, but excellent! Fresh, tasty and perfectly prepared. Finally, the wine selection may not be huge, but they do have  Ch. de Beaucastel 1998 (where else do you find that?) and Gaja Barbaresco 2013 for extremely fair prices.

We were given ample time to review the menu and we ordered for our starters, the friend calamari and my husband had the beet and kale salad. Both items were good, but I was caught off guard by the spice or (come to find out later the jalepeno) fried with the calamari as well as they masked a lemon slice by frying it and putting in with the calamari. It is was so dark that I didn't noticed the lemon fried in with the calamari instead of it being a garnished on the side. 2nd entree we ordered the Canadian Salmon and m husband had the paella. Food was warm not hot as the plates. My salmon was cooked perfectly and hot other than the risotto which was cold. Finally for our 3rd choice we both had the apple bread pudding. I asked is it serve hot  and was told it is served warm, which came out cold.  Other than that everything was good as farvad taste.
